Kernel Routine
==============

I do this everyday to stay up to date with kernel changes and learn
new things.


Morning routine
---------------

- Read latest RSS feeds (phoronix, LWD, lots of blogs from kernel devs)
- Inspect latest patches from the subsystems I follow:

    cd linux-next
    git fetch origin
    git log -p drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ \
          net/core/ \
          include/linux/netdevice.h \
          kernel/bpf/ \
          net/core/filter.c

- Skim over eBPF and mm mailing lists (I focus on RFCs and PATCH 0/X).


Night routine
-------------

Work on the project I am currently working on (a driver, my OS,
learning a tool like yocto, write a compiler....).